0" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3019/regulation/23/g">23(g)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-9a264a516254ad204b9c783fcf7d1de1" marker="F182"><p>Reg. 15(1)(m) revoked (1.4.2013) by <ref eId="cmu7x14w3-00005" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/458">The Council Tax Benefit Abolition (Consequential Provision) Regulations 2013 (S.I. 2013/458)</ref>, <ref eId="cmu7x14w3-00006" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/458/regulation/1">reg. 1</ref>, <ref eId="cmu7x14w3-00007" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/458/schedule/1">Sch. 1</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-3218fb36d46385d506f946e76ddca0ca" marker="F183"><p>Reg. 15(1)(n) substituted (coming into force in accordance with art. 1-3 of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="cq6koacn3-00008" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/422">The Pensions Act 2014 (Consequential, Supplementary and Incidental Amendments) Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/422)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6koacn3-00009" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/422/article/1/2">arts. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6koacn3-00010" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/422/article/21/2">21(2)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-1bff8e233697113f18985d2dad5e9892" marker="F184"><p>Reg. 15(1)(q)(qa) substituted for reg. 15(1)(q) (1.4.2012) by <ref eId="cmpumgt63-00009" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2012/757">The Social Security (Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations 2012 (S.I. 2012/757)</ref>, <ref eId="cmpumgt63-00010" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2012/757/regulation/1/4">regs. 1(4)</ref>, <ref eId="cmpumgt63-00011" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2012/757/regulation/5/3">5(3)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-436360a7a10a0f2f8fd7d7db5bdbc625" marker="F185"><p>Reg. 15(1)(qa) omitted (5.4.2015) by virtue of <ref eId="cq4y3ygu3-00005" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4y3ygu3-00006" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/3">arts. 1(3)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4y3ygu3-00007" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/10/3/a">10(3)(a)</ref> (with <ref eId="cq4y3ygu3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/35/1">art. 35(1)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-515c5b3d09d3428c369b2fab81dc0dbf" marker="F186"><p>Reg. 15(1)(qb) inserted (31.12.2014) by <ref eId="cq4vgz383-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4vgz383-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/2">arts. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4vgz383-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/10/3/b">10(3)(b)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-f715ffd77988326b008d693a65d06c16" marker="F187"><p>Reg. 15(1)(qc) inserted (6.4.2020) by <ref eId="crrqvmu73-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354">The Parental Bereavement Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/354)</ref>, <ref eId="crrqvmu73-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, 