)</ref>, <ref eId="cmputlhp3-00010" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2012/757/regulation/5/4">5(4)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-7db4f831ae906ec18099ea7a13d1a0ad" marker="F234"><p>Word in reg. 17A(2)(i) omitted (5.4.2015) by virtue of <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/3">arts. 1(3)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/10/4/a">10(4)(a)</ref> (with <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00010" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/35/1">art. 35(1)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-18e559dd4a2954d7d96219e25ebda156" marker="F235"><p>Reg. 17A(2)(ia) omitted (5.4.2015) by virtue of <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00015" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00016" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/3">arts. 1(3)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00017" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/10/4/b">10(4)(b)</ref> (with <ref eId="cq4ybc3g3-00018" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/35/1">art. 35(1)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-f58218c059b16350cab6f00228eba584" marker="F236"><p>Reg. 17A(2)(ib) inserted (31.12.2014) by <ref eId="cq4vphq73-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255">The Shared Parental Leave and Statutory Shared Parental Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Order 2014 (S.I. 2014/3255)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4vphq73-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/1/2">arts. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="cq4vphq73-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/3255/article/10/4/c">10(4)(c)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-d07a20981b1e9721737cc5f62a216b9d" marker="F237"><p><ref eId="crrqy1dz3-00006" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792/regulation/17A/2/ic">Reg. 17A(2)(ic)</ref> inserted (6.4.2020) by <ref eId="crrqy1dz3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354">The Parental Bereavement Leave and Pay (Consequential Amendments to Subordinate Legislation) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/354)</ref>, <ref eId="crrqy1dz3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="crrqy1dz3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/354/regulation/10/4">10(4)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-4f33f6ba24df2b049db1b8e17bfb4904" marker="F238"><p>Reg. 17A(3)(e) added (6.10.2003) by <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00025" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197">The State Pension Credit (Consequential, Transitional and Miscellaneous Provisions) (No. 2) Regulations 2002 (S.I. 2002/3197)</ref>, <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00026" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/1/1/b">regs. 1(1)(b)</ref>, <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00027" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/3/1/b">3(1)(b)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-8ef6e49fa942bc95fc58fa70357d5408" marker="F239"><p>Reg. 17A(3)(f) added (for specified purposes and with effect in accordance with reg. 1(2) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="cm5x3ib63-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2009/2655">The Social Security (Miscellaneous Amendments) (No. 4) Regulations 2009 (S.I. 2009/2655)</ref>, <ref eId="cm5x3ib63-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2009/2655/regulation/1/2/c">regs. 1(2)(c)</ref>, <ref eId="cm5x3ib63-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2009/2655/regulation/5/3">5(3)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-7127994301465fb5aa83ce6635a75f5f" marker="F240"><p>Words in reg. 17A(3)(f) substituted (28.4.2014) by <ref eId="cq3hu0sc3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/591">The Social Security (Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations 2014 (S.I. 2014/591)</ref>, <ref eId="cq3hu0sc3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/591/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="cq3hu0sc3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2014/591/regulation/7/3">7(3)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-b5ce80b13e6b1a7a970c944bc4c59a53" marker="F241"><p>Reg. 17A(4A) inserted (6.10.2003) by <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197">The State Pension Credit (Consequential, Transitional and Miscellaneous Provisions) (No. 2) Regulations 2002 (S.I. 2002/3197)</ref>, <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/1/1/b">regs. 1(1)(b)</ref>, <ref eId="cgeqwrmn3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/3/1/c">3(1)(c)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-b59b36307555df0df2e466c548440e69" marker="F242"><p>Reg. 17B(2)(za) inserted (6.10.2003) by <ref eId="cger7