curity (Miscellaneous Amendments) (No. 5) Regulations 2010 (S.I. 2010/2429)</ref>, <ref eId="cmivzf213-00017" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/2429/regulation/1/2">regs. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="cmivzf213-00018" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/2429/regulation/6/b">6(b)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-c0519016682b9ef346151ba64023b3ae" marker="F246"><p>Words in <ref eId="cqalybma3-00033" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792/regulation/17B/4/b">reg. 17B(4)(b)</ref> substituted (3.11.2017) by <ref eId="cqalybma3-00034" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901">The Social Services and Well-being (Wales) Act 2014 and the Regulation and Inspection of Social Care (Wales) Act 2016 (Consequential Amendments) Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/901)</ref>, <ref eId="cqalybma3-00035" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901/article/1">arts. 1</ref>, <ref eId="cqalybma3-00036" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901/article/24">24</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-8899098d557fe8b9c37238127a2e392a" marker="F247"><p>Words in <ref eId="cqalybma3-00006" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792/regulation/17B/4/b">reg. 17B(4)(b)</ref> inserted (3.11.2017) by <ref eId="cqalybma3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901">The Social Services and Well-being (Wales) Act 2014 and the Regulation and Inspection of Social Care (Wales) Act 2016 (Consequential Amendments) Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/901)</ref>, <ref eId="cqalybma3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901/article/1">arts. 1</ref>, <ref eId="cqalybma3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/901/article/9/2/a">9(2)(a)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-c98e1a943fc2977836473727187b14d5" marker="F248"><p>Words in reg. 17B(4)(b) inserted (5.8.2016) by <ref eId="cq6clkhi3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/732">The Children and Young People (Scotland) Act 2014 (Consequential Modifications) Order 2016 (S.I. 2016/732)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6clkhi3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/732/article/1/1">arts. 1(1)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6clkhi3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2016/732/article/4/2/a">4(2)(a)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-e8a7617672d398f823302ffeeebec7d6" marker="F249"><p>Word in reg. 17B(4)(b) omitted (5.1.2009) by virtue of <ref eId="cm4ie0a93-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2008/3157">The Social Security (Miscellaneous Amendments) (No. 7) Regulations 2008 (S.I. 2008/3157)</ref>, <ref eId="cm4ie0a93-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2008/3157/regulation/1/1">regs. 1(1)</ref>, <ref eId="cm4ie0a93-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2008/3157/regulation/4/4/a">4(4)(a)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-6f6fcbea35d8f07fcfd1a9d1f1b2c021" marker="F250"><p>Words in reg. 17B(4)(b) inserted (1.4.2013) by <ref eId="cmu848qs3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/235">The National Treatment Agency (Abolition) and the Health and Social Care Act 2012 (Consequential, Transitional and Saving Provisions) Order 2013 (S.I. 2013/235)</ref>, <ref eId="cmu848qs3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/235/article/1/2">art. 1(2)</ref>, <ref eId="cmu848qs3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/235/schedule/2/paragraph/54/3/a">Sch. 2 para. 54(3)(a)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:T