1"><p>Words in Sch. VI para. 6 inserted (6.10.2003) by <ref eId="cggffbns3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197">The State Pension Credit (Consequential, Transitional and Miscellaneous Provisions) (No. 2) Regulations 2002 (S.I. 2002/3197)</ref>, <ref eId="cggffbns3-00008" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/1/1/b">reg. 1(1)(b)</ref>, <ref eId="cggffbns3-00009" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/schedule/paragraph/13/e">Sch. para. 13(e)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="F" class="commentary F" eId="key-54de52f9540c2d90c94fae8df76e7479" marker="F692"><p>Sch. VI para. 7 added (6.10.2003) by <ref eId="cgdagrhe3-00052" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197">The State Pension Credit (Consequential, Transitional and Miscellaneous Provisions) (No. 2) Regulations 2002 (S.I. 2002/3197)</ref>, <ref eId="cgdagrhe3-00053" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/regulation/1/1/b">reg. 1(1)(b)</ref>, <ref eId="cgdagrhe3-00054" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/3197/schedule/paragraph/13/f">Sch. para. 13(f)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-6e7178164532a1361f1e1415c2923425" marker="C1"><p>Instrument modified (for specified purposes and with effect in accordance with art. 1(2)(l) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="cie92vbk3-00206" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2007/688">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2007 (S.I. 2007/688)</ref>, <ref eId="cie92vbk3-00207" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2007/688/article/26/6">art. 26(6)</ref>, <ref eId="cie92vbk3-00208" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2007/688/schedule/20">Sch. 20</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-cd5ef5bdc64ab0f74c6c72cca18d87e8" marker="C2"><p>Instrument applied (with modifications) (1.10.2010) by <ref eId="cmiv452a3-00025" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/1907">The Employment and Support Allowance (Transitional Provisions, Housing Benefit and Council Tax Benefit) (Existing Awards) (No. 2) Regulations 2010 (S.I. 2010/1907)</ref>, <ref eId="cmiv452a3-00026" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/1907/regulation/16/2/e/iii">reg. 16(2)(e)(iii)</ref><ref eId="cmiv452a3-00027" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/1907/regulation/16/3">(3)</ref> (with <ref eId="cmiv452a3-00028" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2010/1907/regulation/3">reg. 3</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-da2b577e147f84d46eb8e4da9f6f0590" marker="C3"><p>Regulations modified (temp.) (8.4.2020) by <ref eId="crssw16i3-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/409">The Social Security (Coronavirus) (Prisoners) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/409)</ref>, regs. 1, <ref eId="crssw16i3-00008" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/409/regulation/2/2/c">2(2)(c)</ref> (with <ref eId="crssw16i3-00009" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/409/regulation/6/2">reg. 6(2)</ref>); (as amended (12.5.2021) by S.I. 2021/476, reg. 4(6)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-9e6711731cf8a77fd25e004aba9fb75d" marker="C4"><p>Reg. 2 applied (with modifications) (31.12.2020) by <ref eId="c8e2bxic4-00026" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/1209">The Citizens' Rights (Application Deadline and Temporary Protection) (EU Exit) Regulations 2020 (S.I. 2020/1209)</ref>, <ref eId="c8e2bxic4-00027" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/1209/regulation/1/1">regs. 1(1)</ref>, <ref eId="c8e2bxic4-00028" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/1209/regulation/3/3">3(3)</ref>, <ref eId="c8e2bxic4-00029" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/1209/regulation/4/4">4(4)</ref>, <ref eId="c8e2bxic4-00030" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2020/1209/regulation/11/e">11(e)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-a97ac92ba01b11a46fbfbf8d20c1af82" marker="C5"><p>Reg. 2(4)(a)-(e) applied (with modifications) (30.4.2006) by <ref eId="ch79wct63-00018" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2006/1026">The Social Security (Persons from Abroad) Amendment Regulations 2006 (S.I. 2006/1026)</ref>, <ref eId="ch79wct63-00019" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2006/1026/regulation/1">regs. 1</ref>, <ref eId="ch79wct63-00020" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2006/1026/regulation/10/h">10(h)</ref> (with <ref eId="ch79wct63-00021" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2006/1026/regulation/11/2">reg. 11(2)</ref>)</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-fcc75c3b67d5d6c196b913a93b4011d6" marker="C6"><p>Sch. II para. 6(3) formula maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(l) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="d9e4" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up   Rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="cc164779728039" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/l">arts. 1(2)(l)</ref>, <ref eId="cc138897834182" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/25/1/6">25(1)(6)</ref>, <ref eId="cc161165523263" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/13">Sch. 13</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-462b160b45ad282038408f2325888187" marker="C7"><p>Sum in <ref eId="ck3zzh744-00006" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792/schedule/II/paragraph/8/2">Sch. II para. 8(2)</ref> (as it continues to have effect in accordance with S.I. 2017/725 reg. 20)  maintained (11.4.2022 with effect in accordance with art. 1(3)(m) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="ck3zzh744-00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2022 (S.I. 2022/292)</ref>, <ref eId="ck3zzh744-00008" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2022/292/article/30/4">art. 30(4)</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="C" class="commentary C" eId="key-f335e810e69475264f0b7b7f1bce9b7b" marker="C8"><p>Sch. III para. 2(2)(b) sum maintained (coming into force in accordance with art. 1(2)(l) of the amending S.I.) by <ref eId="cq6kv66d3-00276" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260">The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2017 (S.I. 2017/260)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6kv66d3-00277" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/1/2/l">arts. 1(2)(l)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6kv66d3-00278" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/25/1">25(1)</ref><ref eId="cq6kv66d3-00279" class="subref" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/article/25/6">(6)</ref>, <ref eId="cq6kv66d3-00280" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2017/260/schedule/13">Sch. 13</ref></p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262918" marker="M1"><p><ref eId="c00005" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1992/4">1992 c. 4</ref>; section 175 (3) to (5) is applied to provisions of the State Pension Credit Act 2002 by section 19(1) of that Act.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262919" marker="M2"><p><ref eId="c00007" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2001/11">2001 c. 11</ref>; sections 7(4A) and 9(4A) were inserted by the State Pension Credit Act 2002, Schedule 2, paragraphs 45(2) and 46(3).</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262920" marker="M3"><p><ref eId="c00009" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2002/16">2002 c. 16</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262921" marker="M4"><p><ref eId="c00010" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1992/4">1992 c. 4</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262922" marker="M5"><p><ref eId="c00011" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/686">S.I.1983/686</ref>; the relevant amending Instruments are <ref eId="c00012" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/1164">S.I. 1983/1164</ref> and 1984/1675.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262923" marker="M6"><p><ref eId="c00013" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2000/14">2000 c. 14</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262924" marker="M7"><p><ref eId="c00014n1" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1968">S.I. 1987/1968</ref>; the relevant amending Instrument is <ref eId="c00015n1" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1999/3108">S.I.1999/3108</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262925" marker="M8"><p><ref eId="c00016" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1967">S.I. 1987/1967</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="M_M_d64fc131-607a-4671-9eac-eac4d5e89612" marker="M9"><p><ref eId="d15e1" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1996/207">S.I.1996/207</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262928" marker="M10"><p><ref eId="c00019" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1952/52">1952 c. 52</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262929" marker="M11"><p><ref eId="c00020" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1989/45">1989 c. 45</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262930" marker="M12"><p><ref eId="c00021" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1983/20">1983 c. 20</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262932" marker="M13"><p><ref eId="c00023" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1995/46">1995 c. 46</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262933" marker="M14"><p><ref eId="c00024" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1991/56">1991 c. 56</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262934" marker="M15"><p><ref eId="c00025" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1992/14">1992 c. 14</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262944" marker="M16"><p><ref eId="c00034" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1952/52">1952 c. 52</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262945" marker="M17"><p><ref eId="c00035" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1989/45">1989 c. 45</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262946" marker="M18"><p><ref eId="c00036" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1993/47">1993 c. 47</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262948" marker="M19"><p><ref eId="c00038" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1998/14">1998 c. 14</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262949" marker="M20"><p>
                  <i>See</i> in particular paragraph 7(2)(b) of Schedule 8.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262950" marker="M21"><p><ref eId="c00039" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1979/597">S.I. 1979/597</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262952" marker="M22"><p>Sections 30DD and 30E were inserted by section 3(1) of the <ref eId="c00042" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/18">Social Security (Incapacity for Work) Act 1994 (c. 18)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262954" marker="M23"><p><ref eId="c00044" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1979/41">1979 c. 41</ref>; amended by section 24 of the <ref eId="c00045" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1985/53">Social Security Act 1985 (c. 53)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262959" marker="M24"><p><ref eId="c00053" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1837/2">1837 c. 2</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262960" marker="M25"><p><ref eId="c00054" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1937/32">1937 c. 32</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262961" marker="M26"><p><ref eId="c00055" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1952/37">1952 c. 37</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262962" marker="M27"><p><ref eId="c00056" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1972/7">1972 c. 7</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262963" marker="M28"><p><ref eId="c00057" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1975/82">1975 c. 82</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262964" marker="M29"><p><ref eId="c00058" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1998/14">1998 c. 14</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262965" marker="M30"><p><ref eId="c00059" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1992/7">1992 c. 7</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262966" marker="M31"><p><ref eId="c00060" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1993/48">1993 c. 48</ref>;<i>see</i> section 181(1) of that Act.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262967" marker="M32"><p><ref eId="c00061" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1971">S.I.1987/1971</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262969" marker="M33"><p><ref eId="c00063" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1980/46">1980 c. 46</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262970" marker="M34"><p><ref eId="c00064" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2001/4022">S.I. 2001/4022</ref>; the relevant amending Instrument is <ref eId="c00065" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/486">S.I. 2002/486</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262971" marker="M35"><p> <ref eId="c00066" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2002/16">2002 c. 16</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262974" marker="M36"><p>The relevant amending Instrument is <ref eId="c00068" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2000/2629">S.I.2000/2629</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262975" marker="M37"><p><ref eId="c00069" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1969">S.I.1987/1969</ref>; the relevant amending Instruments are <ref eId="c00070" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1988/521">S.I.1988/521</ref> and 670, 1989/1626 and 1991/1600.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262978" marker="M38"><p>Section 171E was inserted by section 6 of the <ref eId="c00074" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/18">Social Security (Incapacity for Work) Act 1994 (c. 18)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262980" marker="M39"><p><ref eId="c00076" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1987/47">1987 c. 47</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262981" marker="M40"><p><ref eId="c00077" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1988/41">1988 c. 41</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262982" marker="M41"><p><ref eId="c00078" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1977/30">1977 c. 30</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262983" marker="M42"><p><ref eId="c00079" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1971">S.I.1987/1971</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262985" marker="M43"><p><ref eId="c00081" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1973/50">1973 c. 50</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262986" marker="M44"><p><ref eId="c00082" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1990/35">1990 c. 35</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262991" marker="M45"><p><ref eId="c00086" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/686">S.I. 1983/686</ref>; amended by <ref eId="c00087" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/1164">S.I. 1983/1164</ref> and 1540 and 1986/628.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262992" marker="M46"><p><ref eId="c00088" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/686">S.I.1983/686</ref>; the relevant amending Instruments are <ref eId="c00089" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1994/715">S.I.1994/715</ref> and 2021.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262993" marker="M47"><p>Section 39A was inserted by section 55 of the <ref eId="c00091" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1999/30">Welfare Reform and Pensions Act 1999 (c. 30)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262994" marker="M48"><p><ref eId="c00092" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1988/1">1988 c. 1</ref>; subsection (1A) was inserted by the <ref eId="c00093" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/9">Finance Act 1994 (c. 9)</ref>, <ref eId="c00094" class="subref operative" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/9/section/81/3">section 81(3)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262995" marker="M49"><p><ref eId="c00095" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1987/1971">S.I. 1987/1971</ref>;<i>see</i> regulations 2(1) and 10.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c262999" marker="M50"><p><ref eId="c00098" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2000/951">S.I.2000/951</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263000" marker="M51"><p><ref eId="c00099" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ssi/2000/200">S.S.I.2000/200</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263001" marker="M52"><p><ref eId="c00100" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/nisr/2000/213">S.R.2000/213</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263002" marker="M53"><p><ref eId="c00101" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1973/50">1973 c. 50</ref>; section 2 was amended by section 25(1) of the <ref eId="c00103" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1988/19">Employment Act 1988 (c. 19)</ref>, by Part I of Schedule 7 to the <ref eId="c00104" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1989/38">Employment Act 1989 (c. 38)</ref> and by section 47(1) of the <ref eId="c00105" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1993/19">Trade Union Reform and Employment Rights Act 1993 (c.19)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263004" marker="M54"><p><ref eId="c00107" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1993/10">1993 c. 10</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263007" marker="M55"><p>Section 30A was inserted by <ref eId="c00110" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1994/18">Social Security (Incapacity for Work) Act 1994 (c. 18)</ref>.</p></note><note ukl:Name="Commentary" ukl:Type="M" class="commentary M" eId="c263009" marker="M56"><p><ref eId="c00112" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/686">S.I.1983/686</ref>; amended by <ref eId="c00113" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/1983/1164">S.I.1983/1164</ref> and 1540 and 1986/628.</p></note></notes><proprietary xmlns:ukm="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/namespaces/metadata" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" source="#"><dc:identifier>http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2002/1792/2025-03-31</dc:identifier><dc:title>The State Pension Credit Regulations 2002</dc:title><dc:type>text</dc:type><dc:format>text/xml</dc:format><dc:language>en</dc:language><dc:publisher>Statute Law Database</dc:publisher><dc:subject scheme="SIheading">SOCIAL SECURITY</dc:subject><dc:modified>2026-03-23</dc:modified><dc:contributor>Expert Participation</dc:contributor><dct:valid>2025-03-21</dct:valid><dc:description>The Regulations contained in this Instrument are made either by virtue of, or in consequence of, provisions in the State Pension Credit Act 2002 (c.16) (“the 2002 Act”). This Instrument is made before the expiry of the period of 6 months beginning with the coming into force of those provisions; the regulations in it are therefore exempt in accordance with section 173(5) of the Social Security Administration Act 1992 from the requirement in section 172(2) of that Act to refer proposals to make Regulations to the Social Security Advisory Committee and are made without reference to that Committee.</dc:description><ukm:SecondaryMetadata><ukm:DocumentClassification><ukm:DocumentCategory Value="secondary"/><ukm:DocumentMainType Value="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument"/><ukm:DocumentStatus Value="revised"/><ukm:DocumentMinorType Value="regulation"/></ukm:DocumentClassification><ukm:Year Value="2002"/><ukm:Number Value="1792"/><ukm:Made Date="2002-07-11"/><ukm:ComingIntoForce><ukm:DateTime Date="2003-10-06"/></ukm:ComingIntoForce><ukm:ISBN Value="0110424751"/><ukm:UnappliedEffects><ukm:UnappliedEffect Modified="2026-03-18T10:31:43Z" Row="6" AffectedExtent="E+W+S" AffectingURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2026/148" RequiresApplied="true" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/effect/key-bcd3e09b41a9e36452f56e535d18c442" AffectedYear="2002" AffectingProvisions="art. 29(2)(a)" AffectedProvisions="reg. 6(1)(a)" AffectingNumber="148" EffectId="key-bcd3e09b41a9e36452f56e535d18c442" AffectingClass="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument" AffectedClass="UnitedKingdomStatutoryInstrument" AffectingEffectsExtent="E+W+S" Type="sum substituted" AffectingYear="2026" AffectedURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792" AffectedNumber="1792"><ukm:AffectedTitle>The State Pension Credit Regulations 2002</ukm:AffectedTitle><ukm:AffectedProvisions><ukm:Section Ref="regulation-6-1-a" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2002/1792/regulation/6/1/a">reg. 6(1)(a)</ukm:Section></ukm:AffectedProvisions><ukm:AffectingTitle>The Social Security Benefits Up-rating Order 2026</ukm:AffectingTitle><ukm:AffectingProvisions><ukm:Section Ref="article-29-2-a" URI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2026/148/article/29/2/a">art. 29(2)(a)</ukm:Section></ukm:AffectingProvisions><ukm:Commencement